# Short Polling â±ï¸

Request at fixed intervals.

```javascript
setInterval(async () => {
    const data = await fetch('/api/messages');
    const messages = await data.json();
    updateUI(messages);
}, 5000); // Every 5 seconds
```

## Pros/Cons:
| Pro | Con |
|-----|-----|
| Simple | Wastes resources |
| Works everywhere | High latency |
| Stateless | Server load |

# Long Polling â³

Server holds request until data available.

## Client:
```javascript
async function poll() {
    try {
        const response = await fetch('/api/updates');
        const data = await response.json();
        handleData(data);
    } finally {
        poll(); // Immediately poll again
    }
}
poll();
```

## Server:
```javascript
app.get('/api/updates', async (req, res) => {
    const data = await waitForNewData(30000); // 30s timeout
    res.json(data);
});
```
